          <td></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="table-note">* REVIEW games show raw model% → post-override% &nbsp;·&nbsp; ★ O/U diverges 6+ pts from Sportsbet line</div>
  </div>
 
  <!-- GAME BY GAME -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">Game by Game</span>
      <div class="section-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="games-grid">
 
      <!-- G1: SEA EAGLES v ROOSTERS — LOWER CONF -->
      <div class="game-card">
        <div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="game-card-header">
            <div>
              <div class="game-num">G1</div>
              <div class="game-matchup">Sea Eagles <span style="color:var(--grey);font-size:18px">v</span> <span class="tipped">Roosters</span></div>
              <div class="game-meta">
                <span>📍 4 Pines Park, Brookvale</span>
                <span>📅 Thu 8:00pm</span>
                <span class="weather-flag">🌧️ Heavy rain + storms forecast</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="flag flag-lower">⬇️ LOWER CONF</span>
          </div>
          <div class="review-block">
            <div class="review-header">⚠️ REVIEW — Model 51% Sea Eagles vs Market 59% Roosters — wet weather coin-flip</div>
            <div class="review-row">
              <span class="review-arrow">Model:</span>
              <span class="review-text">Bye freshness + Seibold desperation at home flips this near even — raw simulation 51% Sea Eagles on adjusted Elo.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="review-row">
              <span class="review-arrow">Market:</span>
              <span class="review-text">Roosters $1.70 (59%) — market respects DCE factor + Roosters won last 3 vs Manly + Roosters W6 L2 away to Sydney clubs on Thursdays.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="review-row">
              <span class="review-arrow verdict">Verdict:</span>
              <span class="review-text"><strong>Override toward market — Roosters.</strong> DCE's first return to 4 Pines as a Rooster is a loaded moment that cuts both ways, but Roosters' Thursday record away to Sydney clubs (6-2) and the structural advantage of a better half in DCE tips it. Wet weather caps the margin. Post-override: 59%.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="game-tip-bar">
            <span class="tip-label">Tip</span>
            <span class="tip-team-lg">ROOSTERS</span>
            <span class="tip-divider">|</span>
            <div class="tip-stat">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Model→Override</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value">51%→59%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-stat">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Market</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value">59%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-stat ml-auto">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Margin</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value">−6</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="game-reasoning">DCE returns to Brookvale and every narrative cuts against an easy Roosters win. But check the numbers: <strong>Roosters are 6-2 away to Sydney clubs on Thursdays</strong>, Sea Eagles are 5-8 at home on Thursdays and have lost their last six Thursday games. Wet weather at Brookvale compresses scoring and suits forward-heavy play — <strong>Manly last 4 vs Roosters at home saw 35 points or less</strong>. In the rain, Manly's forward pack is the only genuine threat. DCE gives Roosters the smarter short kicking game in wet conditions.</div>
          <div class="risk-note">Storm system tracking for Thursday night Sydney — heavy rain and wind confirmed. If conditions are extreme, this tips further toward Sea Eagles' forward pack. Check late mail Friday morning for any late changes.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
 
      <!-- G2: WARRIORS v TIGERS — BANKER -->
      <div class="game-card">
        <div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="game-card-header">
            <div>
              <div class="game-num">G2</div>
              <div class="game-matchup"><span class="tipped">Warriors</span> <span style="color:var(--grey);font-size:18px">v</span> Tigers</div>
              <div class="game-meta">
                <span>📍 Go Media Stadium, Auckland</span>
                <span>📅 Fri 6:00pm</span>
                <span class="weather-flag">🌧️ Rain likely — low pressure system</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="flag flag-banker">🔒 BANKER</span>
          </div>
          <div class="game-tip-bar">
            <span class="tip-label">Tip</span>
            <span class="tip-team-lg">WARRIORS</span>
            <span class="tip-divider">|</span>
            <div class="tip-stat">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Model</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value gold">80%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-stat">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Market</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value">80%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-stat">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Edge</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value edge-nil">nil</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-stat ml-auto">
              <span class="tip-stat-label">Margin</span>
              <span class="tip-stat-value">+24</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="game-reasoning"><strong>Jarome Luai is confirmed out with a knee injury</strong> and Jock Madden — a former Bronco — starts at five-eighth for the Tigers. That's a 10-point Elo penalty before you even factor in Doueihi's hamstring concern listed as a name-only at halfback. Meanwhile the Warriors get <strong>Luke Metcalf back from his ACL early</strong>, CNK returns from concussion, and Pompey is back. Their spine just went from thin to loaded. <strong>Warriors have won 9 straight vs Tigers and 13 straight Friday away games for the Tigers</strong>. This is as structurally locked as it gets without being a certainty.</div>
          <div class="override-note">Override: Model raw 68% → upgraded to 80% to match market. Luai's confirmed absence is a -20 Elo compound penalty that the base simulation underweights given Tigers' already thin Elo base.</div>
          <div class="risk-note">Doueihi playing with a hamstring concern is the only genuine wildcard. If he breaks down in the first half, Tigers could surrender 50+. Monitor for any pre-game news of Doueihi being ruled out.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
 
      <!-- G3: BRONCOS v DOLPHINS — STRONG -->
      <div class="game-card">
        <div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="game-card-header">
            <div>
              <div class="game-num">G3</div>
              <div class="game-matchup"><span class="tipped">Broncos</span> <span style="color:var(--grey);font-size:18px">v</span> Dolphins</div>
              <div class="game-meta">
                <span>📍 Suncorp Stadium, Brisbane</span>
                <span>📅 Fri 8:00pm</span>
